'''Norwegian Folk Music Research Association''' ({{lang-no|[[Norsk Folkemusikklag]]}}) is a [[folk music]] society based in [[Trondheim]], Norway.

It was founded in 1948.<ref name=about>{{cite web|url=http://www.hf.ntnu.no/rff/organisasjonar/engelsk.html|title=About|publisher=Norwegian Folk Music Research Association/Norwegian University of Science and Technology|accessdate=12 June 2009}}</ref> The first president was [[Ole Mørk Sandvik]], who sat until 1965.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|volume=|title=Ole Mørk Sandvik|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Bjørn|last=Aksdal|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Ole_M%C3%B8rk_Sandvik/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=12 June 2009}}</ref> It organizes annual seminars and publishes the yearbook ''Musikk og tradisjon" (Music and tradition). It is a member body of the [[International Council for Traditional Music]] (formerly: the International Folk Music Council).<ref name=about/>

The current president is Bjørn Aksdal, and board members are Maj Vester Larsen, Per Åsmund Omholt, Sveinung Søyland Moen and Anne Svånaug Blengsdalen.<ref name=about/>

